    "The model also employs a GCN to learn medication representation vectors, capturing drug knowledge from a formulated drug network.",
    "However, the model's generalization is limited due to variations in drug combination recommendations among different doctors and regions.",
    "To address this, future research aims to study feature invariance in drug combinations and enhance the algorithm's applicability in real clinical settings.",
    "Chen et al. (2022) proposed a novel computational pipeline called DCMGCN for predicting drug combinations.",
    "The pipeline integrates diverse drug-related information to learn low-dimensional representations of drugs from attributes and similarity networks."
